  "response": "A graduated cylinder, beaker, or volumetric flask are common instruments used to measure volume in a laboratory setting. These instruments typically have markings along the sides to indicate the volume of liquid contained within. For measuring the volume of irregularly shaped objects, a technique called water displacement is often used, which involves measuring the volume of water displaced by the object when it is submerged.",
